        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:11PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Loveland,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, penny size hail, and very heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Murdock, State Route 123 at State Route 132, South Lebanon, Camp
Dennison, Day Heights, Kings Island, Sixteen Mile Stand, Landen,
Dallasburg, Morrow, Springvale, Pleasant Plain, Remington, Mulberry,
Milford, Kings Mills, Montgomery, Woodville, Butlerville, and
Miamiville.

This includes I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 15 and 31.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for
southwestern Ohio. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in effect
until 900 PM EDT for southwestern Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
